[SN]TITLE[SN]
Belfast work incident: Man in a 'critical condition' in hospital

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man is in a critical condition in hospital after a workplace incident at Hayes Fuels in Belfast's Harbour estate.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The man sustained serious injuries after being trapped in machinery on Thursday and was treated at the scene.
The Belfast Trust said the man who was injured is in a critical condition at the Royal Victoria Hospital in Belfast.
The Health and Safety Executive for Northern Ireland (HSENI) said they were investigating.
The incident is reported to have happened just after 12:00 GMT.
